<h1><span id="French_Defence:_Tarrasch_Variation">French Defence: Tarrasch Variation</span></h1>
<p>"3...Nf6 is the most tactical option for black. He doesn't play for a solid position but prefers to complicate matters with dynamic play. Very interesting positions arise, with rich play and fascinating ideas for both sides (GM Andreas Tzermiadianos)". <br>
For those Black players who don't want to play with an isolated d-pawn (at least: not yet), the 3....Nf6 variation is a good
alternative to 3....c5.
</p>
